---

## 🌍 What is this?

Most teams still clean data in scripts, chart it in another tool, and explain it in a third — leaking context (and data) at every handoff.

**UAIDAP** collapses that entire pipeline into one secure workbench: drop in a CSV or Excel file and it detects structural issues, auto-cleans them, classifies the industry it belongs to, renders interactive visualizations, and hands the whole thing to Google Gemini for a plain-English executive briefing — all without your data ever leaving a single, role-secured application.

Built for analysts, admins, and viewers across Finance, Healthcare, Retail, HR, and Education — but genuinely domain-agnostic underneath.

---

## ✨ Highlights

| | |
|---|---|
| 🧹 **Auto-Clean Engine** | Detects missing values, duplicates, and IQR outliers, then fixes them in one click with full before/after diffs |
| 🔐 **Real RBAC** | Admin / Analyst / Viewer roles enforced server-side, backed by bcrypt-salted auth and full session audit logs |
| 📊 **Adaptive Visuals** | Histograms, timelines, scatter plots, and correlation heatmaps that reconfigure themselves per dataset |
| 🤖 **Gemini Copilot** | Ask your data questions in a live terminal; get 10 structured findings + ML model recommendations per upload |
| 🖨️ **One-Click Reporting** | Compiles polished multi-page PDF & PPTX reports straight from the browser canvas |
| 👥 **Team Workspaces** | Secure sharing tokens let viewers explore dashboards without ever touching the raw file |

---

## 🏗️ How it's built

```
Client (React 19 + Recharts + Tailwind)
        │  parses & profiles spreadsheets in-browser (SheetJS) — zero upload latency
        ▼
Server (Express + TypeScript)
        │  auth, RBAC, audit logs, report generation
        ▼
Google Gemini (@google/genai)
        │  structural insight generation, conversational copilot
```

The philosophy: **cheap computations stay client-side, expensive reasoning goes server-side.** Your browser handles instant stats on a 10,000-row sheet in under 100ms; Gemini handles the parts that actually need a brain.

---

## 📁 Project Layout

```
├── src/                  # React frontend — dashboards, charts, copilot UI
├── server/               # Express backend — auth, RBAC, DB, Gemini bridge
├── server.ts             # Entry point
├── .env.example          # Copy to .env and fill in your own keys
└── PROJECT_REPORT.md      # Full technical & academic write-up
```

*(`node_modules/`, `uploads/`, `exports/`, `reports/`, and `profiles/` are intentionally untracked — they're generated at runtime.)*

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

```bash
# 1. Clone it
git clone https://github.com/ARCHITHAK-DS/Universal-AI-Powered-Data-Analytics-Platform.git
cd Universal-AI-Powered-Data-Analytics-Platform

# 2. Install dependencies
npm install

# 3. Configure environment
cp .env.example .env
# → add your Gemini API key and any Firebase config

# 4. Run it
npm run dev
```

Then open the app, upload a spreadsheet, and watch the pipeline run.

